FBIS3-35377 "drnes037_p_94002" FBIS-NES-94-037 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Feb 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Meets President Rabbani BK2302155794 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 GMT 23 Feb 94 BK2302155794 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network Language: Urdu Article Type:BFN [Text] Foreign Minister Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali, who arrived in Kabul today, had detailed talks with Afghan President Professor Borhanoddin Rabbani on the situation in Afghanistan. Afghan sources told Radio Pakistan's Peshawar representative that they held talks on the ways to establish permanent peace and stability in Kabul. The two leaders also held talks on fresh prospects of permanent cease-fire in Kabul to pave the way for peace talks. Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali gave the assurance that Pakistan will continue to help Afghanistan on humanitarian grounds.
